The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 Oran (Algeria), Dec. 17: The Organisation of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (Opec) said the group will slash a record 2 million barrels from its daily production from January 1, while Russia and other countries said they would remove additional barrels from the market. Saudi oil minister Ali Naimi said there was an Opec consensus ahead of a formal agreement for the cut.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 17: Thomas Cook India has decided to allot 35 equity shares for every 100 fully paid-up equity shares held by the existing shareholders on a rights basis.The company has fixed December 27 as the record date for allotting the issue.                            
	 London, Dec. 17: Financial services entity Citigroup will merge the companys investment and corporate banking operations as part of its efforts to streamline and break barriers between its businesses, the Financial Times reported.                                                                                                                         
